<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1043,1131]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,1043,1067]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Elytra unicolored, with long, raised setation completely light-colored and quite uniformly scattered across the whole surface, apex with a small transversal truncation and tiny sutural tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1043,1131]" box="[151,792,1107,1131]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
Paramera and everted endophallus diagnostic (
<figureCitation box="[649,780,1107,1131]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1869,1894]" captionTargetBox="[169,1411,205,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. Pygopleurus hirsutus (Brullé, 1832), habitus and genitalia. 10, male (Laconia, Trachila); 11, male (Corinthia, Galatas); 12, female (Laconia, Trachila); 13, female (Corinthia, Galatas); 14, left paramere in lateral and dorsal view (Corinthia, Galatas); 15, everted endophallus in left lateral view (Laconia, Polovitsa); 16, left genital sclerites of female (Corinthia, Galatas)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458846" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3458846/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Figs. 14–15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1171,1323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,397,1171,1195]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
Distribution (
<figureCitation box="[304,384,1171,1195]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="10.[151,250,938,963]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,181,913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,913]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 17. Pygopleurus hirsutus (Brullé, 1832), geographical, altitudinal, and temporal distribution of records. Red curves showing the expected distribution if the species was uniformly present at all heights and all times (see Material and methods)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3458848/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
This species seems scattered in 
<collectingRegion box="[740,900,1171,1195]" country="Greece" name="Sterea Ellada" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Central Greece</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[951,1089,1171,1195]" country="Greece" name="Peloponnisos" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Peloponnese</collectingRegion>
. Its presence in Messenia is only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[328,374,1204,1228]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1171,1323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[199,425,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis box="[199,425,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Pygopleurus hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported for 
<collectingCountry box="[608,684,1235,1259]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Turkey</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rozner, I. &amp; Rozner, G." box="[721,1000,1235,1259]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" pagination="69 - 100" refId="ref31203" refString="Rozner, I. &amp; Rozner, G. (2009 b) Additional Data to the Lamellicornia Fauna of Turkey (Coleoptera: Lamellicornia). Natura Somogyiensis, 15, 69 - 100" type="journal article" year="2009">Rozner &amp; Rozner (2009b)</bibRefCitation>
. The examination by Marco Uliana (MU) of part of these specimens, preserved in DZCB, revealed that they should be referred to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Petrovitz, 1962)" authorityName="Petrovitz" authorityYear="1962" baseAuthorityName="Petrovitz" baseAuthorityYear="1962" box="[1094,1433,1267,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mithridates">
<emphasis box="[1094,1241,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">P. mithridates</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Petrovitz, R." box="[1256,1425,1267,1291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" pagination="107 - 124" refId="ref30865" refString="Petrovitz, R. (1962) Neue und interessante Scarabaeidae aus dem vorderen Orienten. I. Teil. Reichenbachia, 1 (15), 107 - 124." type="journal article" year="1962">Petrovitz, 1962</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[151,379,1299,1323]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis box="[151,379,1299,1323]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Pygopleurus hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore not known from the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[825,903,1299,1323]" name="Turkey" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Turkey</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1363,1644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,506,1363,1387]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
Eco-ethological notes (
<figureCitation box="[410,493,1363,1387]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="10.[151,250,938,963]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,181,913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,913]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 17. Pygopleurus hirsutus (Brullé, 1832), geographical, altitudinal, and temporal distribution of records. Red curves showing the expected distribution if the species was uniformly present at all heights and all times (see Material and methods)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3458848" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3458848/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[515,745,1363,1387]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" genus="Pygopleurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis box="[515,745,1363,1387]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Pygopleurus hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most early flying species of the genus, appearing as early as 
<date box="[272,388,1392,1419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
20 
<superScript attach="left" box="[298,310,1392,1407]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">th</superScript>
March
</date>
(Lakonia, env. Kardamili, Trachila, 
<quantity box="[781,850,1395,1419]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
) and flying until the end of April (
<date box="[1226,1331,1392,1419]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
30 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1253,1265,1392,1407]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">th</superScript>
April
</date>
, Lakonia, Anavriti, 
<quantity box="[255,340,1427,1451]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
). This early phenology is in accordance with its presence mostly at low altitudes (sea level at 
<collectingRegion box="[1364,1432,1427,1451]" country="Greece" name="Attiki" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Attica</collectingRegion>
, Legrena), although it can reach 
<quantity box="[494,574,1459,1483]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" unit="m" value="1100.0">1100 m</quantity>
(Lakonia, Anavriti). Observations are however biased by the scarcity of records (12) scattered over a wide range. The species appears rare, although this is probably related to its early activity. The very long series (nearly 
<specimenCount box="[420,582,1523,1547]" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" type="generic">200 specimens</specimenCount>
) housed at MHNG and collected by Rudolf Petrovitz near Gythion, indicates that the species can produce abundant and locally dense swarms, as it is the case with other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1819" box="[1147,1282,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Glaphyridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Glaphyridae</taxonomicName>
. Based on our observations, the species was usually encountered as single specimens in 
<taxonomicName box="[939,1029,1588,1611]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Papaver" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[939,1029,1588,1611]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">Papaver</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on Asteracee (yellow Tubuliflorae of genera 
<emphasis box="[229,491,1620,1643]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[229,326,1620,1643]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hyoseris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Hyoseris</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[337,410,1620,1643]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Cymuloporidae" genus="Crepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">Crepis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[421,487,1620,1643]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Picris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Picris</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
within others), and on 
<emphasis box="[738,902,1620,1643]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="161">
<taxonomicName box="[738,899,1620,1643]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cistaceae" genus="Cistus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="10" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="creticus">Cistus creticus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
